Introduction: - The Centrally Sponsored Scheme for Strengthening Teaching, Learning and Outcome of Education System in the State (STARS), funded by the World Bank, is being implemented in the State from the year 2021-22. The expenditure on the scheme is borne by the Central Government and the State Government in the ratio 60:40 respectively. Reference No. By order 1, the Central Government has deposited the second instalment of the current financial year for the Scheduled Tribes Sub-Plan component in the Consolidated Fund of the State. The proposal for devolution of this fund and its corresponding State share is referred to Reference No. 2 has been submitted to the government. A proposal to approve it was under consideration of the government.
The Government's Decisions:

For implementation of the Centrally Sponsored Scheme of Strengthening Teaching, Learning and Outcome of Education System in the State (STARS) funded by the World Bank, the Central Government has released the second instalment of Central share of Rs. 3,91,39, 000 / - (Characters Rs. three crore ninety-one lakh forty-nine thousand) and the corresponding State share of Rs. 2,60,92, 667 / - (Characters Rs. Two crore sixty lakh ninety nine thousand six hundred and sixty seven) totaling to Rs. 6,52,31, 667 / - (Characters Rs. The grant is a conditional grant and the utilization certificate of the funds disbursed earlier has been submitted. The terms and conditions of this grant are set out in the said Government Decision.

3. The Central Government while spending the said fund. The terms and conditions mentioned in the fund distribution order dated 26.03.2025 should be strictly adhered to. Care should be taken to ensure that the funds for items B will be spent within the same limits as those items for which the funds have been allocated, as shown in the table above.

Expenditure on Scheduled Tribe applications under the World Bank-funded Strengthening Teaching, Learning and Outcome of Education System in the State (STARS) scheme should be made from the Single Nodal Account (SNA) account.

5. The State Project Director, Maharashtra Primary Education Council, Mumbai, while spending the said provision, issued the Financial Rules in the Maharashtra Budget Manual, Fiscal Rights Manual as well as the Circular B in the context of the Finance Department in the context of the Tribal Development Department. Strictly follow the instructions given in the Government Circular dated 18.10.2024. It should be ensured that the funds are spent in this year as per the approved plan in line with the existing government policy on expenditure.

6. The Under Secretary / Cell Officer (Cash / Accounts Branch), School Education & Sports Department, Mantralaya, Mumbai is being declared as the Drawing & Disbursing Officer and Joint / Deputy Secretary, School Education Sports Department, Mantralaya, Mumbai as the Controlling Officer for the collection and disbursement of these funds.

The concerned Drawing and Disbursing Officer should withdraw the funds from the treasury and deposit them in the concerned back account under the State Project Director, Maharashtra Council of Elementary Education.

7. Report of expenditure incurred from the provision made available under the head Scheduled Tribes Sub-Plan, Certificate of Fund Utilization, material objectives achieved by title / sub-heading, etc.
The information should be sent to the Tribal Development Department B School Education Department by the 10th of every month by the concerned zonal officer without fail.
8. Ensure that the expenditure incurred in the Scheduled Tribe Sub-Plan area is recorded separately.
So that the government can keep a check on the expenditure on the scheme outside the sub-plan area.

9. The provision made available under the Scheduled Tribes Special Component Programme shall lead to the creation of infrastructure as well as individual benefit schemes in the area as per the framework of the scheme and only individual benefit schemes shall be taken up in the external area of the Scheduled Tribes Sub-Plan.
